description.plain:
Walk the Moon (stylized as WALK THE MOON) is an American rock band From Cincinnati, Ohio. The band was started by lead singer Nicholas Petricca in 2006, taking the name from The Police song Walking on the Moon. The band currently has 3 studio albums and 1 live album.

The band’s current members are Nicholas Petricca (Lead Vocals, Keys) Sean Waugaman (Percussion), and Eli Maiman (Guitar). Kevin Ray (Bass, Background Vocals) was also a member until the band parted ways with him in 2020.  The band has taken in Lachlan West, drummer for The Griswolds, as a touring member of the band.

description.plain:
“Shut Up and Dance” was the lead single from Walk The Moon’s 2014 album, Talking Is Hard.

The single was a major success, and gave Walk the Moon their first top ten pop hit.



Inspired by a true experience and memories of high school, the song makes a deliberate attempt to recreate the bouncy, quirky feel of early 80s pop-rock.

This was one of the last songs they made for the album, written in LA with assistance from Ben Berger and Ryan McMahon of Captain Cuts.

songs.full_title: Anna Sun by WALK THE MOON
songs.title: Anna Sun

description.plain:
“Anna Sun” is the fourth song off of Walk The Moon’s 2012 self titled album. It was named after the band’s professor at Kenyon College. Ms. Anna Sun was happy about this, but she thought that some of the lyrics were too suggestive and asked if they could be changed. Walk The Moon kept the lyrics as they were, but later apologized to her.

The song is all about being in college, playing, and holding on to your inner kid, as lead vocalist Nicholas Petricca says.

description.plain:
“One Foot” is the lead single for Walk the Moon’s fourth studio LP What If Nothing. It was released on September 22, 2017.

During the week of February 10, 2018, the song  peaked at the #2 spot on Billboard’s Rock Airplay chart.
